# BLOX Medical Admin - Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js 14 medical document management application with the following key structure:

## Core Files
- [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with authentication provider
- [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) - Landing page with login form
- [app/dashboard/page.tsx](mdc:app/dashboard/page.tsx) - Main dashboard (protected route)
- [middleware.ts](mdc:middleware.ts) - Authentication middleware

## Authentication
- [lib/auth.ts](mdc:lib/auth.ts) - NextAuth configuration
- [components/SessionProvider.tsx](mdc:components/SessionProvider.tsx) - Session context provider
- [components/LoginForm.tsx](mdc:components/LoginForm.tsx) - Login form component

## Database
- [prisma/schema.prisma](mdc:prisma/schema.prisma) - Database schema with User, Document models
- [lib/prisma.ts](mdc:lib/prisma.ts) - Prisma client configuration

## Components
- [components/Header.tsx](mdc:components/Header.tsx) - Reusable header with BLOX AI branding
- [components/DocumentRepository.tsx](mdc:components/DocumentRepository.tsx) - Main document management interface
- [components/DocumentModal.tsx](mdc:components/DocumentModal.tsx) - Modal for adding/editing documents

## API Routes
- [app/api/documents/route.ts](mdc:app/api/documents/route.ts) - Document CRUD operations
- [app/api/documents/[id]/route.ts](mdc:app/api/documents/[id]/route.ts) - Individual document operations
- [app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts](mdc:app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts) - Authentication endpoints

## Key Features
- Document upload to AWS S3
- Real-time document management
- Search and filtering
- Category-based organization
- User authentication with NextAuth